// LOCATIONS Crashed Maintenance Ship A master battery is required to activate the basic Craftbot inside. You can find farming equipment in the area nearby. The yellow box in the cockpit will contain a logbook. Haymaze A maze made out of hay bales. There is nothing special in there. Packing Station The billboard shows you how to use it. You will need a vacuum pump attached to a large chest on your vehicle. Connect a button to the vacuum pump and fill the chest with the item you want to give to the packing station. A bar at the station will tell you how much to put in the plant to receive one crate of the item. \n \nThere are two types of packing stations. One takes vegetables and one fruit. \nTake the crates to a hideout. Ruin There are multiple variations of ruins. They usually contain damaged crates and ruin chests. Haybots spawn inside or near ruins as well as piles of hay. Hit them with the sledgehammer or shoot them with the spudgun to reveal a damaged crate. Not every pile of hay has one underneath it. Farmer Shack Farmer Shacks are shacks found next to the roads. You can find soil, seeds and lots of building material in them. The farmers used to live and sell their stuff here. Warehouse This is the most dangerous area in survival mode. You need a warehouse key to get in. You can get the key by killing the big red boss farmbot. \n \nWarehouses can spawn with two, three and four floors. All types have a lootroom at the top with 5 epic damaged crates and a chest with items. Therefore its recommended to go to the two floor warehouses. \n \nTapebots are inside and near the warehouses and will shoot you. It\\\'s recommended to have a spudgun before you go in there. The red tapebot in the top floor will shoot explosives. Farmbots will spawn at the base of 4 floor warehouses. Mechanic Station The mechanic station has a large illuminated wrench on top of it\'s roof. You have to get a master battery from the bunkhouse rooms next to the mechanic station. After you put it in the designated slot you will activate the crafting console. It\'s used to craft the Crafting Bot, Dressbot, Cookbot, Refinebot and Resource Collector. Farmers Hideout Bring your fruit / vegetables crates or the hideout dropoff / cage guy to the hideout. You can put the things on top of a pad there and press the button next to it. This will suck in the resources in and you will be able to spend them on your purchase.\n\nYou can buy items like the spudgun or rare seeds at the hideout. Autumn Forest This is a great place to find cotton or even caged farmers. Burned Forest Here you can find ember, which is used for crafting. Just hammer the trees and you will receive it. Chemical Plant Don\'t fall into the pink lake, this is the chemicals. You can use a bucket or pump the get the chemicals out of the lake. Forest A great source for wood and stone. It\'s recommended to come with a sawblade and a drill to get the most out of it. Ruin City This is a perfect spot for finding damaged crates and component kits. Be careful there are a lot of haybots, even the red farmbots are there. Water Plant The area around the water plant is very flat and there is a lot of water, which makes it a perfect spot for your farm, as it\'s easy to defend as well. Underwater Here you can find the glue clams, crude oil and the Glowb. This is a small light illuminating, green / yellow colored creature. It will drop glow when you feed it 15 cardboard blocks. Stone Woc A paddock with a woc made out of stone which is surrounded by a bunch of real wocs. You can find it in the middle of the forest. Oil Lake The oil lake can be found in a desert like biome and you can use it to pump oil.
